  "text": "The Fallopian tubes are highly specialized and serve a number of essential functions in the reproductive process. The functional Fallopian tubes capture ovulated ova and transport sperm and embryos [CITATION_1] . Tubal pathology is among the most common causes of female infertility and the primary diagnosis in approximately 30-35% of infertile women [CITATION_2] .",
